2026-04-30T08:48:11.6405024Z             "body": "## Summary\nAdd support for disabling SMTP probes, HTTP/HTTPS probes, and DNSBL queries via command-line flags, environment variables, and a new web UI options panel. This allows operators to run ednsv in restricted network environments where outbound traffic on certain ports or to certain services is blocked, and enables users to opt out of specific check categories without re-running the entire validation.\n\n## Key Changes\n\n- **Web UI Options Panel**: New collapsible \"Validation options\" section with checkboxes for SMTP probes, HTTP/HTTPS lookups, and DNSBL queries, plus a text field for custom DKIM selectors. Options persist to localStorage so users in restricted networks don't have to re-untick boxes on every visit.\n\n- **CLI Flags**: Added `--no-smtp`, `--no-http`, `--no-dnsbl`, and `--restricted-network` (convenience preset) flags to disable check categories at runtime.\n\n- **Server Configuration**: New environment variables (`EnableSmtpProbes`, `EnableHttpProbes`, `EnableDnsbl`) allow operators to centrally disable categories for the entire instance. Client-side toggles use AND-logic: if the operator has disabled a category, clients cannot re-enable it.\n\n- **API Endpoints**:\n  - POST `/api/validate` now accepts an `options` object in the request body with the three network-category toggles and additional DKIM selectors.\n  - GET `/api/validate/{domain}` now supports query parameters (`?noSmtp=true`, `?noHttp=true`, `?noDnsbl=true`, `?restricted=true`, `?dkimSelectors=a,b,c`) mirroring CLI flags.\n  - New GET `/api/defaults` endpoint surfaces the built-in DKIM selector list so the UI can pre-fill the options field.\n\n- **Check Skipping**: All affected checks now return an Info-severity \"Skipped\" result when their network category is disabled, rather than attempting to run with missing probe data. This includes SMTP checks (TLS cert, banner, STARTTLS, submission ports, postmaster/abuse, open relay, catch-all), HTTP checks (MTA-STS, BIMI, security.txt, Certificate Transparency), and DNSBL checks (IP/hostname/domain blocklists).\n\n- **Prefetch Optimization**: SMTP probe prefetch is now skipped entirely when `EnableSmtpProbes=false`, though MX IP resolution still occurs for DNS-only checks.\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n- Network-category toggles default to `true` (enabled) for backward compatibility.\n- The `ValidationOptions` class now includes `EnableSmtpProbes`, `EnableHttpProbes`, and `EnableDnsbl` properties.\n- A new `CheckContext.SkippedResult()` helper method standardizes the \"skipped\" response format across all affected checks.\n- DKIM selector handling: if the user hasn't customized the list, the UI fetches and displays server defaults; if customized, the custom list is sent in validation requests and stored in localStorage.\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01RS9QVLbjPkAasik6fwJVc8",
